
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
uv init visceral_fat --package
cd visceral_fat
uv add --dev pytest
new.py -tp "Visceral Fat Calculator" visceral_fat_calculator.py
mv visceral_fat_calculator.py src/visceral_fat
mv visceral_fat_calculator.py src/visceral_fat
rm Makefile
rm -rf tests/
touch src/visceral_fat/ __init__.py

--------The above file structure will work, but I changed it for this version--------


To run:
cd <path to project>/visceral_fat/src/visceral_fat
uv run visceral_fat_calculator.py
uv run visceral_fat_calculator.py -h  #help
uv run visceral_fat_calculator.py -g  #gui
uv run pytest
To run only 1 test:
uv run pytest visceral_fat_calculator_test.py::test_get_male_visceral_fat_by_convesion


Using tkinter for GUI:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vusUfPBsggw&list=PLs3IFJPw3G9IiHm9PEP1UaMtuvACmxVMj&index=3


Add this to your imports to look in current directory:
See: src/visceral_fat/visceral_fat_calculator_test.py
Look in current directory for visceral_fat_calculator module
import sys
sys.path.append(".")

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NPJUl9I_t6E


Regular expressions I used:
positive integer: regex = r"^(\s*(?!0)|[1-9]\d*)$"
positive float:  regex = r"^(\s*(?!0)|[1-9][0-9]*)[.]?\d*$"
Name:  regex = r"^(\s*(?!0)|[\-a-zA-Z]+)$"



